Since we use the API IProject#open(...) I guess there was a problem in Platform
Resources ....

This may be related to the compile errors that occurred in JDT UI. I have a 
copy of the nightly build in which these are fixed and I am able to run the 
JavaProjectTests with no errors. Are you able to reproduce the error when the 
compile errors are fixed?

I fail to see how compile errors in JDT UI would affect JDT Core (JDT Core
doesn't require JDT UI).

I assumed that JDT core had extension points that JDT UI may have plugged 
into. This would introduce a dependency. Are you saying there are no such 
extension points? Of course, you are right, the cause may be something else. 
My main point in that I was unable to reproduce the error on the code in HEAD. 
We're a bit light on Core committers today (due to travel, sickness, etc) so 
unless we can reproduce it, further investigation may have to wait.

I can investigate when I get back tomorrow.  This kind of stack trace doesn't
provide much evidence because someone else could be ending the rule in that
thread to cause the error.  If it's still reproducible, I should be able to
track it down.  I can't think of any recent changes in core that would cause this.
I confirm that JDT UI doesn't plug into any JDT Core extension point.

I have not been able to reproduce a failure. Without a reproducible case it is
difficult to track down further. I'll leave this open a little while to see if
it occurs again.
